{"action":"created","issue":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/53137","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/53137/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/53137/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/53137/events","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/53137","id":2110220747,"node_id":"PR_kwDOABkWpM5lk9Kx","number":53137,"title":"Implement empty! for Channel","user":{"login":"KronosTheLate","id":61620837,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjYxNjIwODM3","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/61620837?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/KronosTheLate","html_url":"https://github.com/KronosTheLate","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KronosTheLate/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KronosTheLate/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KronosTheLate/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KronosTheLate/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KronosTheLate/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KronosTheLate/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KronosTheLate/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KronosTheLate/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KronosTheLate/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":184008807,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWwxODQwMDg4MDc=","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/labels/multithreading","name":"multithreading","color":"fbca04","default":false,"description":"Base.Threads and related functionality"}],"state":"open","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":1,"created_at":"2024-01-31T14:27:25Z","updated_at":"2024-02-02T10:13:54Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","active_lock_reason":null,"draft":false,"pull_request":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/pulls/53137","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/53137","diff_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/53137.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/53137.patch","merged_at":null},"body":"What is says on the box. ~Returning the number of elements removed is analogous to `write`, and can provide useful information.~ I ended up changing the implementation to call `empty!` on `c.data`, instead of call `take!` until the channel was empty. I expect this to be significantly more efficient than removing the elements one-by-one.

I have not changed any changelog. I am also not certain if I should have used any `@atomic` annotations, which I saw a lot of in this file. But I would not know how.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/53137/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/53137/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null},"comment":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/comments/1923490883","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/53137#issuecomment-1923490883","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/53137","id":1923490883,"node_id":"IC_kwDOABkWpM5ypiRD","user":{"login":"KronosTheLate","id":61620837,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjYxNjIwODM3","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/61620837?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/KronosTheLate","html_url":"https://github.com/KronosTheLate","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KronosTheLate/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KronosTheLate/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KronosTheLate/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KronosTheLate/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KronosTheLate/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KronosTheLate/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KronosTheLate/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KronosTheLate/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KronosTheLate/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2024-02-02T10:13:53Z","updated_at":"2024-02-02T10:13:53Z","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"Did you have an opinion of whether or not it makes sense to return the number of elements removed? Pro: Potentially useful information, hard to query without using internals (fields directly, or unexported functions). Con: Breaks with general API for `empty!`, where the empty collection is returned.

Personally I am leaning towards returning the number of elements removed, because it is potentially quite useful in a context where you would manually call `empty!` on a channel. Not doing it to preserve an API seems a bit puritanical to me, when real practicalities are sacrificed. Also, if the channel is being emptied, the user will have a handle to it (variable bound to it) in the call to `empty!` anyways, making that return-value rather useless.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/comments/1923490883/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null}}

